    <note>Wang(2) Lin(2) [11521] When his father Shenzhi [11520] died, he killed his elder brother, Yanhan (not in dataset) and made himself ruler of Min. His original mingzi was Yanjun. He, in turn, was killed by his son, Chang [11522], and the eunuch Huangcheng shi, Li(2) Fang (not in dataset). See Renming Da cidian for the time being. Lin was a believer in witchcraft, shamanism and taoism.</note>
